HEADWORD: Diner-out
<hw>Din"er-out`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who often
takes his dinner away from home, or in company.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A brilliant <qex>diner-out</qex>, though but a curate.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

